    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of picture caption with Dec 3 article on Russia's likely rejection of Kyoto treaty, regarding cause of global warming</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A picture caption on Wednesday about Russia's likely rejection of the Kyoto treaty intended to curb global warming misidentified a cause of the warming. It is the emission of heat-trapping gases including carbon dioxide, not industrial toxic dust. The caption also referred incorrectly to 1990 data that were used to formulate the treaty. The data showed that Russia generated 17.4 percent of the heat-trapping gases released by industrialized countries, not 17.4 percent of the world's pollution.</p>
      </block>
